tspan.tspan: The number of annotated objects that were correctly detected by the model.
Specifically, a true positive is counted if an annotation overlaps significantly
(IoU >= 0.50) with at least one prediction of confidence > 0.50. When
counting true positives, two annotations cannot share the same prediction.
The number of incorrect detections (of confidence > 0.50) made by the model.
A prediction is considered a false detection if it does not overlap significantly
(IoU >= 0.50) with any annotation (or only overlaps significantly with
annotations that have been assigned to other predictions).
The number of annotated objects that were missed by the model.
A false negative is counted if an annotation does not overlap significantly
(IoU >= 0.50) with any prediction (of confidence > 0.50) (or only overlaps
significantly with predictions that have been assigned to other annotations).
